Alig nganjij, daag ngankiya.
Alig nga-n-j-ij, daag nga-n-k-i-ya.
feel.bad 1-TR-do-PFV sleep 1-TR-FUT-do-FUT
‘I am tired, I am going to bed.’


Nganangoorribi iila.
oo-n-k-ngoorribi iila
3-TR-chase dog
`He/She'll chase the dog.'


a-ngg-arr-a-marr-a

Second person minimal and third person (both minimal and augmented) forms vary for future marking. Second person forms also vary for transitivity.
The prefix is a- for transitive verbs, and nga- for intransitive ones, as illustrated
by the pair in (11.9). Second person augment imperatives and futures
have the form arr-. (pp. 426-427)
        
        Past/Present (Non-future) Tense:
          2min: mi-
          2aug: goo-
          3min, 3aug: i-
       
       oonkowa
       oo-n-k-o-wa
       3-TR-FUT-poke-FUT
       `He/she’ll poke it.’
        
        Future Tense:
          2min (transitive): a-
          2min (intransitive): nga-
          2aug: a-
          3min, 3aug: oo-
       
       Nganangoorribi iila.
       oo-na-nga-ngoorribi iila
       3-TR-chase dog
       `He/She will chase the dog.'

        Minangoorribi iila.
        mi-na-ngoorribi iila
        2MIN.fut-TR-chase dog
        `You chase the dog.' 
        
        
       
       
        No Tense Distinction:
          1min: ng(a)-
          1aug: a-
          1+2min a-
